The paper deals with gossip algorithms for the rumor spreading problem, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the efficiency and randomness of the algorithms, which could fall under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents an algorithm that solves the k-local broadcast problem, which involves communication between nodes, and could fall under the categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
